article_title: Midterm Elections 2014: Little Enthusiasm, Heated Rhetoric Mark N.Y. Governor Race
article_text:
New Yorkers head to the polls on Tuesday after a campaign season in which the race for governor generated little enthusiasm but a fair amount of heated rhetoric.

Democratic Gov. Andrew Cuomo had leads of 20 percentage points or more in public polls over his Republican opponent, Westchester County Executive Rob Astorino, as he seeks a second...
